<subSubSection id="6C0DF727513ABB0311967E477BBE64A1" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="D1DC7E40FE05D6BD2F264721F103DED0" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="874F5EFDD45BFFF97CFF0530FDB0B869" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<taxonomicName id="8629652B4A6435ED766C34CD97DAAC50" authorityName="Iljin, Fl. USSR 6: 875" authorityYear="1936" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Corispermum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Corispermum gelidum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gelidum">
<emphasis id="01A5F94ABCDA9771E1A2BCBC1394AE32" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Corispermum gelidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="54E8CD7F60DE141B66FF629314734A8B" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. pamiricum var. pilocarpum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" rank="variety" species="pamiricum" variety="pilocarpum">C. pamiricum var. pilocarpum</taxonomicName>
are synonymised here for the first time due to the presence of stellate hairs on the fruit surface. Other anatomical characters of the fruit are similar and overlapping (compare with 
<bibRefCitation id="06FB3392739A9117D12B4A694BCCCBD1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.37.37103" author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="63 - 87" refId="B103" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, 2007b. Fruit anatomy and its taxonomic significance in Corispermum (Corispermoideae, Chenopodiaceae). Willdenowia 37 (1): 63 - 87, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.37.37103" title="Fruit anatomy and its taxonomic significance in Corispermum (Corispermoideae, Chenopodiaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.37.37103" volume="37" year="2007 b">Sukhorukov 2007b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CBDDB55253B51F68D4AC056877C0A504" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.172.2.3" author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" refId="B113" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, Zhang, M, Nilova, MV, 2014. The carpology and taxonomy of some Chinese Corispermum. Phytotaxa 172(2): 81-93. https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.172.2.3" title="The carpology and taxonomy of some Chinese Corispermum. Phytotaxa 172 (2): 81 - 93." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.172.2.3" year="2014">Sukhorukov et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). However, the authentic specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="7991C2349702F84BAC99848C383CE646" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. pamiricum var. pilocarpum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" rank="variety" species="pamiricum" variety="pilocarpum">C. pamiricum var. pilocarpum</taxonomicName>
possess a small (ca. 0.15 mm) fruit wing, whereas the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="93E048275872FF047945480205ABA1CE" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. gelidum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" rank="species" species="gelidum">
<emphasis id="0546E1C0D8422D754EECFDB17E22117D" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">C. gelidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a prominent (0.3-0.4 mm) wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B82C61660776C6D709B82AFDC472072D" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph id="409AA1779D61C630883BDE52CBBC1E4C" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C6E1798FC5C726329220ADC4DDCE2DB" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
Annual up to 20 cm, glabrescent. Leaves linear to narrowly oblong, up to 3.0 
<normalizedToken id="6344A229852DE28F06E68BA13AF4DA60" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5(0.7) cm. Inflorescence short. Bracts shorter than leaves, lanceolate, (almost) completely covering the fruit, appressed to the stem. Fruit 2.6-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="89619A0ACD457251C8D1E411D6914F2E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.7-2.0 mm, 0.40-0.60 mm thick, flat or folded adaxially, with triangular apex terminating in slightly emarginate beak, with stellate hairs and mostly warty (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2DA552F7F96E8A5661548FE943D4A2BE" captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. SEM micrographs of Corispermum fruits: A C. lhasaense B C. lepidocarpum C C. gelidum D C. tibeticum. Magnification: 30 x." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.114.27301.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/260777" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">36C</figureCitation>
), sometimes with groups of dark-brown tanniniferous cells. Wing 0.15-0.45 mm, entire to dentate, broadly triangular in cross-section. Sclereids in the medium fruit part composed of 1-2 layers located parallel to the fruit axis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37A403AE39E777EBC47F51FDFA0D546A" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="3E1F4C3CB201BF6BB9CAE8474A4B7665" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21908D6B6FDB84CD7B3A00F79E0BD144" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Sandy places at altitudes of 3500-4800 m.</paragraph>
